
test_omc: Exercise OMC/OTP from user container

Commands:

    * Read OMC = reads from OTP memory using OMC api.
        read omc [offset] [size]
      where:
        offset: offset from which to read from.
        size: size in bytes to read.

    * Read MMR = reads from memory mapped location using direct access.
        read mmr [address] [size]
      where:
        address: address from which to read from.
        size: size in bytes to read.

    * Write OMC = writes to OTP memory using OMC api.
        write omc [offset] [value]
      where:
        offset: offset to write to.
        value: value to write.

    * Write MMR = writes to memory mapped location using direct access.
        write mmr [address] [value]
      where:
        address: offset to write to.
        value: value to write.

    * Root create = creates root in the specified index.
        root create [index] [hash] [permissions]
      where:
        index: index to create into.
        hash: hash to write.
        permissions: permissions to write.

    * Root obliterate = obliterates root at the specified index.
        root obliterate [index]
      where:
        index: index to create into.

IMPORTANT: when using these commands, it should be noted that there is a
limitation in regards the size which can be read and/or written.
This limitation matches the size of the register which is going to be
read/written.

Command to load the container:

$ mwtest.py -c 100 run test_omc.img

How to send a command:

$ cmtest cmd -f 100 [command to send]

Example command to create root 6 with hash given a a random value and
permissions equal to zero:

$ cmtest cmd -f 100 root create 6 %8fa473a673aad565aef729ca680bcbfe3c4fec60f092e7ecd4b651399cf3e90b %000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000

Example command to obliterate root 6:

$ cmtest cmd -f 100 root obliterate 6

Command to unload the container:

$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
